text.__SUMMARY__: Common names: Solomon Island tree boa.Candoia bibroni australis is a nonvenomous boa subspecies endemic to the Solomon Islands.
text.Description: Adults can grow up to 2 to 5 feet (0.6 to 1.5 m) in total length (including tail). Mature females are typically much larger than the males. Longevity is 10 years or more.
text.Geographic range: Found in the Solomon Islands.The type locality given is "Nouvelle-Calédonie" (New Caledonia).
text.Feeding: The young will prey on small frogs and lizards, while adults will feed on larger prey such as smaller rodents.
